        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">digital</ENAMEX> photography and the images <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">quantitatively</ENAMEX> analyzed
        using 
        Total <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Labâ¢ Phoretics</ENAMEX> gel analysis
        software (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Nonlinear Dynamics</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Durham</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">North Carolina</ENAMEX>). This
        application was found to be most accurate, user-friendly,
        and efficiently handled dual tier gels. Furthermore, as
        with other packages, it allowed simple export of the
        numerical results to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Excel</ENAMEX> spreadsheets. A database was
